          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-24 13:52:58" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to dedicate to the service of and to loyalty to deity</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to consecrate</Gloss>
                <Gloss>consecration</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to dedicate to God</Gloss>
                <Gloss>dedication</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in certain contexts ἁγιάζω[a] and ἁγιασμός suggest resulting moral behavior, the emphasis is not upon a manner of life but upon religious activity and observances which reflect one’s dedication or consecration to God. Accordingly, in {S:04600100200018} one may translate ἁγιάζω as who have given themselves to God or who serve God with a whole heart.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
