              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to feel reverence for or to honor as holy</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to hallow</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to regard as holy</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to honor as holy</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is impossible to employ an expression such as ‘your name’ as a reference for God himself. Therefore, it may be necessary to translate this expression in {S:04000600900022} as ‘may you be reverenced as holy’ or even ‘may you be acknowledged as God.’</Comments>
